taircase, and knocked on Darwin’s door. Darwin, already shaven and washed, was eating scrambled eggs and bacon; Marshall, a fat textbook on political economy, lay open near his plate.

“Got another letter today?” sternly inquired Martin.

“From my tailor,” said Darwin chewing juicily.

“Sonia’s handwriting isn’t too good,” remarked Martin.

